Task 2: Building a Student Digital Portfolio
For the second task, I established my professional digital presence by selecting LinkedIn, GitHub, and Kaggle as my core platforms. I chose LinkedIn to begin networking with VIT Bhopal alumni and industry experts in the cloud domain, ensuring my education section accurately reflects my current degree in Cloud Computing and Automation. I utilized GitHub to host my initial coding projects, creating a specialized "Profile README" to introduce my technical interests and academic goals to the global developer community. Lastly, I selected Kaggle to stay updated on data-driven automation trends and to begin practicing with real-world datasets.

Over the next four years, I plan to use these platforms as a dynamic "living resume." On GitHub, I will consistently commit code and automation scripts to document my progress as a cloud engineer. On LinkedIn, I intend to share certifications and internship milestones to build a recognizable professional brand. By maintaining these profiles starting in my first year, I am ensuring that by the time I reach my final year, I will have a comprehensive, time-stamped record of my technical growth and achievements that is readily accessible to top-tier recruiters and internship coordinators.
